&quot;To a strong amazon nation!&quot;, she cried.  Quickly, the amazon rode her chestnut horse up near the others, but not next to them.  An amazon who rarely met up with her sister amazons.  Penthesilea had long allied herself with the Trojans.  But word had gotten out that a war was declared.  And Penth was not one to ignore it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 392<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/13/01 7:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~War~</span><hr size=1>  A war without the Queen of the Assassins, was well, not smart to say the least. For the last couple of months, the immortal amazon assassin had been playing things safe, staying out of the cross fire, and staying out of the fights. But one thing be known, you can't keep a good woman [or man] down, and welp, that blood lust was going to proove it in this war. <br>
<br>
 Dawnithinia Rivent Darkshade, had made one pitstop after leaving Orio-Pata; for this war. Where do you think she went? Ares could tell you, or more aless, that's where she went. The favored assassin, against the gods.. why not stop at a temple for worship.<br>
<br>
 But now, behind the other Queens, and Princesses, the Queen of the assassins; The Queen of Orio-Pata, made her appearence.<br>
<br>
 Tight black leathers, doned her body. They were old, and still smelt of the days when war was a common thing, and blood shed brought about the multiple massacres. Leather elven boots, were as always, sheathed with four black hilted daggers. Travelling up the assassin's legs, on each outter thigh, was a leather sheath, holding, you guessed it, two black hilted knives. The sword.. was placed securely across her back. Not a weapon had a shimmering glow to it, not a one. The security of camoflouge was needed, this was just to proove it.<br>
<br>
 The amazon queen, rode comfortably on a black stallion. The Orio-Pata symbol blazed into the skin on its right hind quarter. A war markings similar to the one that covered the rider's face [Half Tiger, Half Wolf, for those who want details.], adorned the saddle, the reigns, and the bridle.<br>
<br>
 Blazing crimson eyes, shifted to Alysia, as she pulled the horse to a stop along side her friend, and athelfi. It was not by choice that she was here, but by force. This was the amazon nation, and she was apart of it. When she'd entered her life into it, she had vowed life and soul to it. No fear of death would stop her from prooving her greatest devotion.<br>
<br>
 A deep breath, and then a content, focused sigh escaped from under the mask. There wasn't a moment, when Dawn herself didn't think of Wulf, Lilla, or the things she'd just left behind. She'd come back alive, no immortal could die unless they wanted, too. With the right mind, Dawn wasn't about to die because she got into some war, with some overly egotistical gods, oh and goddesses.<br>
<br>
 It was time to play dirty, and everyone knows, Dawn can get down and dirty with the best of them; if she isn't one of the best.<br>
<br>
<br>
